  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A prospective study on 50 consecutive patients who are going to have a lower body lift
      procedure is performed. Measures include comorbidities and complications. Risk factors
      assessed including patient age, gender, highest lifetime body mass index (BMI) (BMI max),
      current BMI, excess weight loss (EWL), type of weight loss and nicotine consumption.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
